Question 1

ar1_gen <- function( nobs, sd,phi=1) {
  y <- rep(0,nobs)
  for(t in 2:nobs) {
    y[t] <- y[t-1] + rnorm(1, mean = 0, sd=sd)
  }
  return(y)
}


test_statistic <- rep(0,1000)
p_values <- rep(0,1000)
for(i in 1:1000) {
  x <- ar1_gen(nobs = 50, sd=1)
  y <- ar1_gen(nobs = 50, sd=1)
  test_statistic[i] <- summary(lm(y~x))$coefficients[2,3]
  p_values[i] <- summary(lm(y ~ x))$coefficients[2, 4]
}

Plot a density for the t-statistics captured along with that of a t(48) distribution

plot(density(test_statistic), col="pink", ylim = c(0,.4), main="Density Plot")
x_t <- seq(-4,4,.01)
lines(x_t, dt(x_t, df = 48), col = 'forestgreen')
legend("topright", legend = c("T-Statistics", "t(48)"), col = c("pink", "forestgreen"), lty = c(1, 2))

t.test(test_statistic)
## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  test_statistic
## t = -1.39, df = 999, p-value = 0.1648
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.55931109  0.09548964
## sample estimates:
##  mean of x 
## -0.2319107
critical_value <- qt(0.975, df = 48)
significant_t_statistics <- sum(abs(test_statistic) > critical_value)
percentage_significant <- (significant_t_statistics / length(test_statistic)) * 100
cat("Percentage of significant t-statistics:", percentage_significant, "%\n")
## Percentage of significant t-statistics: 66.9 %

Adding more covariates

test_statistic_x1 <- rep(0,1000)
test_statistic_x2 <- rep(0,1000)
test_statistic_x3 <- rep(0,1000)
test_statistic_x4 <- rep(0,1000)
for(i in 1:1000) {
  x1 <- ar1_gen(nobs = 50, sd=1)
  x2 <- ar1_gen(nobs = 50, sd=1)
  x3 <- ar1_gen(nobs = 50, sd=1)
  x4 <- ar1_gen(nobs = 50, sd=1)
  y1 <- ar1_gen(nobs = 50, sd=1)
  model <- lm(y1 ~ x1 + x2 + x3 + x4)
  

  test_statistic_x1[i] <- summary(model)$coefficients[2, 3]
  test_statistic_x2[i] <- summary(model)$coefficients[3, 3]
  test_statistic_x3[i] <- summary(model)$coefficients[4, 3]
  test_statistic_x4[i] <- summary(model)$coefficients[5, 3]
}

critical_value <- qt(0.975, df = 48)

percentage_significant_x1 <- sum(abs(test_statistic_x1) > critical_value) / length(test_statistic_x1) * 100
percentage_significant_x2 <- sum(abs(test_statistic_x2) > critical_value) / length(test_statistic_x2) * 100
percentage_significant_x3 <- sum(abs(test_statistic_x3) > critical_value) / length(test_statistic_x3) * 100
percentage_significant_x4 <- sum(abs(test_statistic_x4) > critical_value) / length(test_statistic_x4) * 100


cat("Percentage of significant t-statistics for x1:", percentage_significant_x1, "%\n")
## Percentage of significant t-statistics for x1: 52.4 %
cat("Percentage of significant t-statistics for x2:", percentage_significant_x2, "%\n")
## Percentage of significant t-statistics for x2: 50.4 %
cat("Percentage of significant t-statistics for x3:", percentage_significant_x3, "%\n")
## Percentage of significant t-statistics for x3: 51.2 %
cat("Percentage of significant t-statistics for x4:", percentage_significant_x4, "%\n")
## Percentage of significant t-statistics for x4: 47.6 %

#series 1
ggplot(data=data) +
  geom_line(aes(x=date, y=series_one), colour="hotpink") +
  ggtitle("Series 1") +
  labs(y = "Series 1", x = "Date")

Differencing

data <- data %>%
  mutate(first_diff_series_1 = difference(series_one, difference = 1))


ggplot(data=data) +
  geom_line(aes(x=date, y=first_diff_series_1), colour="hotpink") +
  ggtitle("1st Differenced Series 1") +
  labs(y = "Series 1", x = "Date")
## Warning: Removed 1 row containing missing values (`geom_line()`).

Detrending

model <- lm(series_one ~ date, data = data)
detrend_series1 <- data %>%
  mutate(detrended_series1 = series_one - predict(model))


ggplot(data=detrend_series1) +
  geom_line(aes(x=date, y=detrended_series1), colour="hotpink") +
  ggtitle("Detrended Series 1") +
  labs(y = "Series 1", x = "Date")
